<h3>Component::<code>text-input</code></h3>

<h4>Overview</h4>
<div class="row">
    <desc>
        The <code>text-input</code> control is the simplist of the set of atomic input controls. Since it's primary function is capturing <em>string</em> values
        it is worth noting that an input control left blank will be equal to an empty string not a <em>null</em> value (this is opposite to a numeric input). 
        If you would prefer that an empty string is viewed as a <em>null</em> value then just set the <code>emptyIsNull</code> property to true.
        
    </desc>
    <desc>
        The rules available to a <code>text-input</code> component are:
        <ul>
            <li>
                <code>lengthLimit</code> - 
                triggers when the control has surpassed the allowable length (set in component as 'length' but tranlated into HTML as 'size') and 
                blocks the control from growing beyond the stated size.
            </li>
            <li>
                <code>lengthWarn</code> - 
                triggers when the control has surpassed the allowable length (set in component as 'length' but tranlated into HTML as 'size') but
                does not prohibit further input. Instead is will trigger any animation, sound, or status change 
            </li>
            <li>
                <code>invalidEmail</code> - 
                triggers when the control moves into an invalid representation of an email address (although ignores a null value); no visual 
                or auditory effects by default (although of course they can be added). Intended use it more as an action hook for container to 
                take action on this condition.  
            </li>
        </ul>        
    </desc>
</div>

